    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1996 Porsche 911 Carrera (993), representing the pinnacle of air-cooled engineering. This example features the M64/21 3.6L flat-six equipped with the Varioram induction system, delivering linear torque across the rev range. The G50 6-speed manual transaxle exhibits crisp gate engagement with no synchro hesitation. Chassis rigidity is absolute, supported by the Weissach-designed LSA multi-link rear suspension. The underbody is clinically dry, showing zero seepage from the crankcase or chain covers. Finished in pristine Polar Silver over black leather, the exterior retains its factory-applied Bosch lighting and original VIN-matching panels. Technical documentation is exhaustive, confirming a rigorous maintenance schedule. Ready for a comprehensive PPI to verify its concours-level mechanical and cosmetic integrity.",
